Queen is hiring a sous chef who can develop technical expertise using ‘the most organic and unique sources’ from her Royal gardens . 
  The successful applicant will have to travel to various Royal residences for three months of the year . 
  Based mainly at Buckingham Palace the job pays around £28,000-a-year . 
  Former personal chef Darren McGrady revealed the Queen has simple tastes in food . 
  She likes Special K, chocolate cake and jam sandwiches . 
  The Queen also enjoys venison or salmon from Balmoral in Scotland . 
 